%20course%2C%20given%20the%20nature%20of%20his%20victory%20in%20the%20November%20Presidential%20elections.%20The%20liberal%20media%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most%20vocal%20opponents%20of%20Trump%20and%20his%20policies%2C%20but%20in%20the%20end%2C%20it%20is%20now%20forced%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20it%20remains%20out%20of%20touch%20with%20mainstream%20America.%20And%20Trump%20will%20not%20let%20them%20forget%20this%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20few%20days%2C%20Trump%20has%20been%20outlining%20his%20administration's%20policy%20priorities%20and%20making%20it%20quite%20clear%20that%20he%20sees%20no%20need%20to%20go%20back%20on%20most%20aspects%20of%20his%20campaign%20promises.%20Looking%20back%20on%20his%20win%20against%20Vice-President%20Kamala%20Harris%20last%20month%2C%20Trump%20has%20asserted%20that%20his%20campaign%20resonated%20with%20the%20country%20by%20focusing%20on%20immigration%2C%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20other%20key%20issues%20that%20he%20has%20argued%20were%20more%20in%20tune%20with%20voters'%20concerns%20than%20the%20Democratic%20message.%20%E2%80%9CI%20don't%20think%20they%20%5Bthe%20Democrats%5D%20got%20the%20feel%20of%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20Trump%20has%20asserted.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20the%20Republican%20Party%20has%20become%20the%20party%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccommon%20sense%E2%80%9D.%20Not%20only%20did%20he%20win%20the%20popular%20mandate%20this%20time%2C%20but%20the%20Republicans%20will%20also%20be%20in%20control%20of%20both%20the%20US%20House%20of%20Representatives%20and%20the%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Bring%20It%20Back'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20feels%20vindicated%20of%20his%20assessment%20of%20the%20popular%20mood%20and%20in%20his%20interviews%2C%20therefore%2C%20he%20is%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20he%20intends%20to%20take%20his%20agenda%20forward.%C2%A0The%20tone%2C%20however%2C%20is%20softer%20and%20gentler%20in%20his%20interviews%20and%20he%20is%20talking%20of%20uniting%20the%20country%20by%20working%20to%20ensure%20its%20success.%20In%20his%20words%3A%20%E2%80%9CI'm%20really%20looking%20to%20make%20our%20country%20successful.%20I'm%20not%20looking%20to%20go%20back%20into%20the%20past.%20I'm%20looking%20to%20make%20our%20country%20successful.%20Retribution%20will%20be%20through%20success.%20If%20we%20can%20make%20our%20success%E2%80%94his%20country%20successful%2C%20that%20would%20be%20my%20greatest%E2%80%94that%20would%20be%20such%20a%20great%20achievement.%20Bring%20it%20back.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20has%20also%20talked%20of%20the%20possibility%20that%20his%20former%20political%20opponents%20like%20Liz%20Cheney%20could%20face%20jail%20time.%20He%20has%20also%20underlined%20that%20he%20believes%20%E2%80%9Ca%20vast%20majority%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20nearly%201%2C200%20people%20who%20have%20either%20pleaded%20guilty%20or%20were%20found%20guilty%20at%20trial%20for%20crimes%20connected%20to%20the%20January%206%20attack%20should%20not%20be%20in%20jail.%20He%20will%20begin%20reviewing%20possible%20pardons%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20first%20hour%E2%80%9D%20he%20assumes%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EImmigrants%20Prime%20Target%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmigration%20seems%20to%20be%20his%20core%20priority%2C%20with%20illegal%20immigration%20being%20described%20by%20him%20as%20%E2%80%9Can%20invasion%20of%20our%20country%E2%80%9D%20requiring%20the%20use%20of%20the%20National%20Guard%20and%20local%20law%20enforcement%20along%20with%20the%20military%20in%20deportation%20processes%2C%20something%20that%20can%20be%20legally%20challenging.%20He%20is%20threatening%20nations%20not%20willing%20to%20take%20back%20immigrants%20with%20tariffs%2C%20underscoring%20that%20%E2%80%9Cif%20they%20don't%20take%20them%20back%2C%20we%20won't%20do%20business%20with%20those%20countries%2C%20and%20we%20will%20tariff%20those%20countries%20very%20substantially%E2%80%9D.%20Trump%20has%20also%20reiterated%20his%20campaign%20pledge%20to%20abolish%20birthright%20citizenship%2C%20which%20is%20guaranteed%20by%20the%2014th%20Amendment%2C%20and%20hinted%20that%20he%20might%20try%20to%20overturn%20this%20right%20through%20executive%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20domestic%20issues%20that%20have%20emerged%20as%20key%20for%20Trump%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20his%20administration%20are%20managing%20high%20inflation%2C%20reviving%20the%20US%20oil%20industry%20(%E2%80%9CDrill%2C%20Baby%2C%20Drill%E2%80%9D)%2C%20and%20the%20downsizing%20of%20the%20federal%20Department%20of%20Education%20and%20transferring%20most%20responsibilities%20to%20state%20governments.%20Trump%20is%20calling%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvirtual%20closure%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20in%20Washington%2C%E2%80%9D%20something%20that%20would%20require%20Congressional%20acquiescence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EAn%20'Agreement'%20On%20Ukraine%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20foreign%20policy%20front%20too%2C%20he%20is%20making%20the%20dividing%20line%20with%20his%20predecessor%20quite%20clear.%20He%20has%20underlined%20his%20%E2%80%9Cvehement%E2%80%9D%20disagreement%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20policy%20of%20allowing%20Ukraine%20to%20use%20US-provided%20long-range%20weapons%2C%20called%20Army%20Tactical%20Missile%20Systems%2C%20or%20ATACMS%2C%20to%20strike%20deep%20into%20Russian%20territory%2C%20arguing%20that%20this%20policy%20was%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20escalating%20this%20war%20and%20making%20it%20worse%E2%80%9D.%20He%20continues%20to%20suggest%20that%20he%20does%20not%20intend%20to%20abandon%20Ukraine.%20But%20the%20way%20to%20do%20this%2C%20for%20Trump%2C%20is%20to%20reach%20an%20agreement%2C%20as%20the%20war%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctragedy%E2%80%9D%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstaggering%E2%80%9D%20number%20of%20people%20killed%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20he%20has%20something%20new%20to%20say.%20In%20his%20last%20term%2C%20he%20had%20called%20for%20%E2%8