I.%20The%20startup%20has%20relied%20on%20humans%20to%20do%20much%20of%20the%20work%2C%20former%20employees%20say.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20with%20a%20robot%20arm%20carrying%20a%20stack%20of%20papers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674e18fc9e9761932b4a3bc2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEvenUp%20vaulted%20past%20a%20%241%20billion%20valuation%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20AI%20will%20help%20automate%20personal%20injury%20demands.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFormer%20employees%20told%20BI%20the%20company%20has%20relied%20on%20humans%20to%20do%20much%20of%20the%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEvenUp%20says%20it%20uses%20a%20combination%20of%20AI%20and%20humans%20to%20ensure%20accuracy%2C%20and%20its%20AI%20is%20improving.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp%20vaulted%20past%20a%20%241%20billion%20valuation%20on%20the%20idea%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-frontier-crowded-winners-losers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prnewswire.com%2Fnews-releases%2Fevenup-raises-135m-in-series-d-funding-and-launches-new-products-to-help-level-the-playing-field-in-personal-injury-cases-302270003.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eautomate%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20lucrative%20part%20of%20the%20legal%20business.%20Former%20employees%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20startup%20has%20relied%20on%20humans%20to%20complete%20much%20of%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp%20aims%20to%20streamline%20personal-injury%20demands%20and%20has%20said%20it%20is%20one%20of%20the%20fastest-growing%20companies%20in%20history%20after%20jumping%20from%20an%20%2485%20million%20valuation%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-unicorn-startups-created-this-year-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunicorn%3C%2Fa%3E%20status%20in%20an%20October%20funding%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20upload%20medical%20records%20and%20case%20files%2C%20and%20EvenUp's%20AI%20is%20supposed%20to%20sift%20through%20the%20vast%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-synthetic-data-industry-debate-over-fake-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20pulling%20out%20key%20details%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20an%20accident%20victim%20should%20be%20owed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20EvenUp's%20investors%20has%20described%20its%20%26quot%3BAI-based%20approach%26quot%3B%20as%20representing%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pitchclub.io%2Fp%2Fnfx-s-crystal-ball-spotting-evenup-before-the-ai-boom%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equantum%20leap%20forward.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%2C%20at%20least%20so%20far%2C%20is%20that%20human%20staff%20have%20done%20a%20significant%20share%20of%20that%20work%2C%20and%20EvenUp's%20AI%20has%20been%20slow%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20slack%2C%20eight%20former%20EvenUp%20employees%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20interviews%20over%20the%20late%20summer%20and%20early%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20employees%20said%20they%20witnessed%20numerous%20problems%20with%20EvenUp's%20AI%2C%20including%20missed%20injuries%2C%20hallucinated%20medical%20conditions%2C%20and%20incorrectly%20recorded%20doctor%20visits.%20The%20former%20employees%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20to%20preserve%20future%20job%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20claim%20during%20the%20interview%20process%20and%20training%20that%20the%20AI%20is%20a%20tool%20to%20help%20the%20work%20go%20faster%20and%20that%20you%20can%20get%20a%20lot%20more%20done%20because%20of%20the%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20former%20EvenUp%20employee%20who%20left%20earlier%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BIn%20practice%2C%20once%20you%20start%20with%20the%20company%2C%20my%20experience%20was%20that%20my%20managers%20told%20me%20not%20even%20to%20use%20the%20AI.%20They%20said%20it%20was%20unreliable%20and%20created%20too%20many%20errors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20other%20former%20employees%20also%20said%20they%20were%20told%20by%20supervisors%20at%20various%20points%20this%20year%20not%20to%20use%20EvenUp's%20AI.%20Another%20former%20employee%20who%20left%20this%20year%20said%20they%20were%20never%20told%20not%20to%20use%20the%20AI%2C%20just%20that%20they%20had%20to%20be%20vigilant%20in%20correcting%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20100%25%20told%20it's%20not%20super%20reliable%2C%20and%20I%20need%20to%20have%20a%20really%20close%20eye%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20former%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp%20told%20BI%20it%20uses%20a%20combination%20of%20humans%20and%20AI%2C%20and%20this%20should%20be%20viewed%20as%20a%20feature%2C%20not%20a%20bug.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20combined%20approach%20ensures%20maximum%20accuracy%20and%20the%20highest%20quality%2C%26quot%3B%20EvenUp%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20Rami%20Karabibar%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BSome%20demands%20are%20generated%20and%20finalized%20using%20mostly%20AI%2C%20with%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20human%20input%20needed%2C%20while%20other%20more%20complicated%20demands%20require%20extensive%20human%20input%20but%20time%20is%20still%20saved%20by%20using%20the%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22314252bd-84e4-423a-b2aa-f5d010ac06dc%5C%22%3EAI's%20virtuous%20cycle%20of%20improvement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20common%20strategy%20for%20AI%20companies%20to%20rely%20on%20humans%20early%20on%20to%20complete%20tasks%20and%20refine%20approaches.%20Over%20time%2C%20these%20human%20inputs%20are%20fed%20into%20AI%20models%20and%20related%20systems%2C%20and%20the%20technology%20is%20meant%20to%20learn%20and%20improve.%20At%20EvenUp%2C%20signs%20of%20this%20virtuous%20AI%20cycle%20have%20been%20thin%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20the%20former%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20didn't%20seem%20to%20me%20like%20the%20AI%20was%20improving%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20former%20staffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20AI%20is%20improving%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Karabibar%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20saves%20more%20time%20today%20than%20it%20did%20a%20week%20ago%2C%20it%20saved%20more%20time%20a%20week%20ago%20than%20it%20did%20a%20month%20ago%2C%20and%20it%20saved%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20a%20month%20ago%20than%20it%20did%20last%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205142aad-bcb8-48b7-ac29-98980f4f16ff%5C%22%3EA%20broader%20concern%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp's%20situation%20highlights%20a%20broader%20concern%20as%20AI%20sweeps%20across%20markets%20and%20boardrooms%20and%20into%20workplaces%20and%20consumers'%20lives.%20Success%20in%20generative%20AI%20requires%20complex%20new%20technology%20to%20continue%20to%20improve.%20Sometimes%2C%20there's%20a%20gap%20between%20the%20dreams%20of%20startup%20founders%20and%20investors%20and%20the%20practical%20reality%20of%20this%20technology%20when%20used%20by%20employees%20and%20customers.%20Even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-artificial-intelligence-bet-doubts-marc-benioff-satya-nadella-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20has%20struggled%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewith%20some%20practical%20implementations%20of%20its%20marquee%20AI%20product%2C%20Copilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20AI%20is%20adept%20at%20sorting%20and%20interpreting%20vast%20amounts%20of%20data%2C%20it%20has%20so%20far%20struggled%20to%20accurately%20decipher%20content%20such%20as%20medical%20records%20that%20are%20formatted%20differently%20and%20often%20feature%20doctors'%20handwriting%20scribbled%20in%20the%20margins%2C%20said%20Abdi%20Aidid%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20who%20has%20built%20machine-learning%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20scan%20the%20data%2C%20it%20gets%20scrambled%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20having%20AI%20read%20the%20scrambled%20data%20is%20not%20helpful%2C%26quot%3B%20Aidid%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20BI%20asked%20EvenUp%20about%20the%20role%20of%20humans%20in%20producing%20demand%20letters%2C%20one%20of%20its%20key%20products.%20After%20the%20outreach%2C%20the%20startup%20responded%20with%20written%20answers%20and%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.evenuplaw.com%2Fblog%2Fleveraging-ai-human-review-in-demand-letters-the-evenup-difference%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20clarified%20the%20roles%20employees%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20AI%20models%20trained%20on%20generic%20data%20can%20handle%20some%20tasks%2C%20the%20complexity%20of%20drafting%20high-quality%20demand%20letters%20requires%20much%20more%20than%20automation%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAt%20EvenUp%2C%20we%20combine%20AI%20with%20expert%20human%20review%20to%20deliver%20unmatched%20precision%20and%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup's%20spokesman%20declined%20to%20specify%20how%20much%20time%20its%20AI%20saves%20but%20told%20BI%20that%20employees%20spend%2020%25%20less%20time%20writing%20demand%20letters%20than%20they%20did%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20spokesman%20also%20said%2072%25%20of%20demand%20letter%20content%20is%20started%20from%20an%20AI%20draft%2C%20up%20from%2063%25%20in%20June%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d6c15b4-5519-47b4-9187-4d9ca22bed45%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20father's%20injury%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp%20was%20founded%20in%202019%2C%20more%20than%20two%20years%20before%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20launched%20the%20generative%20AI%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarabibar%2C%20Raymond%20Mieszaniec%2C%20and%20Saam%20Mashhad%20started%20EvenUp%20to%20%26quot%3Beven%26quot%3B%20the%20playing%20field%20for%20personal-injury%20victims.%20Founders%20and%20investors%20often%20cite%20the%20story%20of%20Mieszaniec's%20father%2C%20Ray%2C%20to%20explain%20why%20their%20mission%20is%20important.%20He%20was%20disabled%20after%20being%20hit%20by%20a%20car%2C%20but%20his%20lawyer%20didn't%20know%20the%20appropriate%20compensation%2C%20and%20the%20resulting%20settlement%20%26quot%3Bwas%20insufficient%2C%26quot%3B%20Lightspeed%20Venture%20Partners%2C%20one%20of%20EvenUp's%20investors%2C%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flsvp.com%2Fstories%2Finvesting-in-evenup-on-a-mission-to-closing-the-justice-gap%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrite-up%20about%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20trained%20a%20machine%20to%20be%20able%20to%20read%20through%20medical%20records%2C%20interpret%20the%20information%20it's%20scanning%20through%2C%20and%20extract%20the%20critical%20pieces%20of%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DXEzdwxC9xmQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMieszaniec%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20last%20year.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20the%20first%20technology%20that%20has%20ever%20been%20created%20to%20essentially%20automate%20this%20entire%20process%20and%20also%20keep%20the%20quality%20high%20while%20ensuring%20these%20firms%20get%20all%20this%20work%20in%20a%20cost-effective%20manner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22608d2fb5-669f-44b8-bb8f-6c03165ead18%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvenUp%20technical%20errors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20eight%20former%20EvenUp%20employees%20told%20BI%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20this%20process%20has%20been%20far%20from%20automated%20and%20prone%20to%20errors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20pretty%20much%20double-check%20everything%20the%20AI%20gives%20you%20or%20do%20it%20completely%20from%20scratch%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20former%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20software%20has%20missed%20key%20injuries%20in%20medical%20records%20while%20hallucinating%20conditions%20that%20did%20not%20exist%2C%20according%20to%20some%20of%20the%20former%20employees.%20BI%20found%20no%20instances%20of%20these%20errors%20making%20it%20into%20the%20final%20product.%20Such%20mistakes%2C%20if%20not%20caught%20by%20human%20staff%2C%20could%20have%20potentially%20reduced%20payouts%2C%20three%20of%20the%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp's%20system%20sometimes%20recorded%20multiple%20hospital%20visits%20over%20several%20days%20as%20just%20one%20visit.%20If%20employees%20had%20not%20caught%20the%20mistakes%2C%20the%20claim%20could%20have%20been%20lower%2C%20one%20of%20the%20former%20staffers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20employees%20recalled%20EvenUp's%20AI%20system%20hallucinating%20doctor%20visits%20that%20didn't%20happen.%20It%20also%20has%20reported%20a%20victim%20suffered%20a%20shoulder%20injury%20when%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20their%20leg%20was%20hurt.%20The%20system%20also%20has%20mixed%20up%20which%20direction%20a%20car%20was%20traveling%20%E2%80%94%20important%20information%20in%20personal-injury%20lawsuits%2C%20the%20former%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20pull%20information%20that%20didn't%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20software%20has%20also%20sometimes%20left%20out%20key%20details%2C%20such%20as%20whether%20a%20doctor%20determined%20a%20patient's%20injury%20was%20caused%20by%20a%20particular%20accident%20%E2%80%94%20crucial%20information%20for%20assigning%20damages%2C%20according%20to%20some%20of%20the%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20a%20big%20moneymaker%20for%20the%20attorneys%2C%20and%20the%20AI%20would%20miss%20that%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp's%20spokesman%20acknowledged%20that%20these%20problems%20cited%20by%20former%20employees%20%26quot%3Bcould%20have%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20especially%20in%20earlier%20versions%20of%20its%20AI%2C%20but%20said%20this%20is%20why%20it%20employs%20humans%20as%20a%20backstop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22efdc5d4b-74bd-432a-8def-907313d820f5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20customer%20and%20an%20investor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp%20did%20not%20make%20executives%20available%20for%20interviews%2C%20but%20the%20spokesman%20put%20BI%20in%20touch%20with%20a%20customer%20and%20an%20investor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Simon%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20the%20Simon%20Law%20Group%2C%20said%20EvenUp's%20AI%20has%20made%20his%20personal-injury%20firm%20more%20efficient%2C%20and%20using%20humans%20reduces%20errors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20appreciate%20that%20because%20I%20would%20love%20to%20have%20an%20extra%20set%20of%20eyes%20on%20it%20before%20the%20product%20comes%20back%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Simon%20said.%20%26quot%3BEvenUp%20is%20highly%2C%20highly%20accurate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Hinkfuss%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Bain%20Capital%20Ventures%2C%20said%20she%20appreciated%20EvenUp's%20human%20workers%20because%20they%20help%20train%20AI%20models%20that%20can't%20easily%20be%20replicated%20by%20competitors%20like%20OpenAI%20and%20its%20ChatGPT%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20building%20novel%20datasets%20that%20did%20not%20exist%20before%2C%20and%20they%20are%20automating%20processes%20that%20significantly%20boost%20gross%20margins%2C%26quot%3B%20Hinkfuss%20wrote%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e2a8473-5161-4203-a40c-a2bd1d5bdda1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELong%20hours%2C%20less%20automation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20former%20EvenUp%20employees%20said%20a%20major%20reason%20they%20were%20drawn%20to%20the%20startup%20was%20because%20they%20had%20the%20impression%20AI%20would%20be%20doing%20much%20of%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20thought%20this%20job%20was%20going%20to%20be%20really%20easy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20of%20the%20former%20staffers.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20that%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20like%20you%20check%20work%20that%20the%20AI%20has%20already%20done%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%2C%20these%20people%20said%2C%20was%20that%20they%20had%20to%20work%20long%20hours%20to%20spot%2C%20correct%2C%20and%20complete%20tasks%20that%20the%20AI%20system%20could%20not%20handle%20with%20full%20accuracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20my%20coworkers%20would%20work%20until%203%20a.m.%20and%20on%20weekends%20to%20try%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20what%20was%20expected%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20former%20employee%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp's%20AI%20could%20be%20helpful%20in%20simple%20cases%20that%20could%20be%20completed%20in%20as%20little%20as%20two%20hours.%20But%20more%20complex%20cases%20sometimes%20required%20eight%20hours%2C%20so%20a%20workday%20could%20stretch%20to%2016%20hours%2C%20four%20of%20the%20former%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20work%20on%20Christmas%20and%20Thanksgiving%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20of%20these%20people.%20%26quot%3BThey%20%5Bthe%20managers%5D%20acted%20like%20it%20should%20be%20really%20quick%20because%20the%20AI%20did%20everything.%20But%20it%20didn't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvenUp's%20spokesman%20said%20candidates%20are%20told%20upfront%20the%20job%20is%20challenging%20and%20requires%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20writing.%20He%20said%20retention%20rates%20are%20%26quot%3Bin%20line%20with%20other%20hyper-growth%20startups%26quot%3B%20and%20that%2040%25%20of%20legal%20operations%20associates%20were%20promoted%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20recognize%20that%20working%20at%20a%20company%20scaling%20this%20fast%20is%20not%20for%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20spokesman.%20%26quot%3BIn%20addition%2C%20as%20our%20AI%20continues%20to%20improve%2C%20leveraging%20our%20technology%20will%20become%20easier%20and%20easier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20continued%20importance%20of%20human%20workers%2C%20the%20spokesman%20noted%20that%20EvenUp%20hired%20a%20vice%20president%20of%20people%20at%20the%20end%20of%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fevenup-ai-errors-hallucinations-former-employees-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734084001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674e18fc9e9761932b4a3bc2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fevenup-ai-errors-hallucinations-former-employees-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20staffers%20told%20BI%20they%20witnessed%20numerous%20problems%20with%20EvenUp's%20AI%2C%20including%20missed%20injuries%20and%20hallucinated%20medical%20conditions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bbergman%40insider.com%20(Ben%20Bergman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A51%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fevenup-ai-errors-hallucinations-former-employees-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20financially%20independent%20real%20estate%20investor%20explains%20the%20'live-in%20BRRRR'%20strategy%20he's%20using%20to%20eventually%20sidestep%20capital%20gains%20and%20shield%20up%20to%20%24250%2C000%20in%20profit%20from%20tax%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22dion%20mcneeley%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675b309057df667cc5a5d4d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDion%20McNeeley%20owns%2016%20units%20across%20seven%20properties%20in%20Washington.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Dion%20McNeeley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDion%20McNeeley%20used%20a%20buy-and-hold%20strategy%20to%20build%20a%2016-unit%20rental%20portfolio.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20experimented%20with%20the%20BRRRR%20method%20by%20purchasing%20and%20renovating%20a%20duplex%20in%202023.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20could%20eventually%20sell%20the%20property%20and%20leverage%20an%20IRS%20rule%20to%20avoid%20capital%20gains%20tax.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDion%20McNeeley%20spent%20over%20a%20decade%20carefully%20building%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-financial-freedom-former-truck-driver-father-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eportfolio%20of%20rental%20properties%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20throughout%20Washington%20State.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20sold%20a%20property.%20I've%20never%20done%20a%20cash-out%20refinance.%20I've%20never%20taken%20out%20a%20home%20equity%20line%20of%20credit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20the%20slow%2C%20boring%20investor%3A%20Save%20up%20a%20down%20payment%2C%20buy%20the%20next%20place%3B%20save%20up%20a%20down%20payment%2C%20buy%20the%20next%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20buy-and-hold%20strategy%20allowed%20him%20to%20quit%20his%20day%20job%20in%202022%20and%20retire%20in%20his%20early%2050s.%20He%20had%20enough%20rental%20income%20coming%20in%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-prepare-for-recession-real-estate-investor-early-retirement-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehis%2016-unit%20portfolio%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20sustain%20his%20lifestyle%20and%20then%20some.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202023%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20experiment%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-flipping-brrrr-real-estate-investing-strategies-mortgage-rates-biggerpockets-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBRRRR%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20short%20for%20buy%2C%20rehab%2C%20rent%2C%20refinance%2C%20repeat%20%E2%80%94%20method%20and%20purchased%20a%20beat-up%20duplex%20outside%20Seattle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20people%20should%20start%20investing%20with%20the%20BRRRR%20strategy.%20There%20are%20so%20many%20mistakes%20that%20you%20can%20make%20with%20the%20after-repair%20value%2C%20the%20estimated%20cost%2C%20and%20the%20estimated%20time%20of%20doing%20repairs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McNeeley%2C%20who%20scaled%20his%20portfolio%20by%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20strategy%20that%20involves%20buying%20a%20multi-family%20property%2C%20living%20in%20one%20unit%2C%20and%20renting%20out%20the%20rest.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20do%20any%20BRRRRs%20to%20reach%20financial%20freedom%20and%20retire%20early.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20early%20retiree%20shared%20his%20experience%20doing%20a%20%26quot%3Blive-in%20BRRRR%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20he%20lived%20in%20the%20duplex%20while%20doing%20renovations%20%E2%80%94%20including%20how%20he%20found%20the%20property%20and%20added%20value%2C%20and%20the%20strategy%20he%20could%20eventually%20use%20to%20sell%20and%20sidestep%20capital%20gains%20tax.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f114854-ed00-4d95-9734-a9968c4c7e3a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFinding%20a%20deal%20by%20focusing%20on%20'days%20on%20market'%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20step%20to%20successfully%20executing%20a%20BRRRR%20is%20finding%20a%20distressed%20property%20with%20potential.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReal%20estate%20investors%20tend%20to%20agree%20that%20you%20make%20your%20money%20on%20the%20purchase%20%E2%80%94%20not%20on%20the%20sale.%20To%20land%20a%20good%20deal%20in%202023%2C%20McNeeley%20focused%20on%20one%20specific%20metric%20when%20combing%20through%20listings%3A%20the%20number%20of%20days%20a%20property%20has%20been%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20watching%20what%20are%20called%20'days%20on%20market%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Generally%20speaking%2C%20the%20longer%20a%20home%20has%20been%20sitting%2C%20the%20better%20chance%20you%20have%20of%20negotiating%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20seller.%20%26quot%3BLong%26quot%3B%20is%20relative%20to%20the%20average%20days%20on%20market%2C%20which%20varies%20by%20location.%20%26quot%3BIn%20some%2C%20it's%2010%3B%20in%20others%2C%20it's%2030.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20area%20in%20Washington%2C%20he%20said%20the%20average%20is%20between%20six%20and%20nine%20days.%20He%20narrowed%20his%20search%20to%20properties%20that%20were%20listed%20for%20at%20least%20three%20times%20the%20average%2C%20or%20about%2030%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20duplex%20he%20ended%20up%20buying%20had%20been%20on%20the%20market%20for%20over%20100%20days%20and%20was%20listed%20for%20%24500%2C000.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20offered%20400%2C000%20because%20that's%20the%20number%20that%20made%20sense%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McNeeley.%20After%20about%20two%20months%20of%20negotiating%2C%20he%20got%20it%20for%20the%20number%20he%20wanted.%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20moved%20from%20400.%20It%20went%20from%20500%20to%20477%20to%20444%20to%20422.%20When%20I%20got%20another%20offer%20accepted%20somewhere%20else%2C%20I%20contacted%20them%20to%20say%20I%20was%20pulling%20my%20offer.%20They%20said%2C%20'We'll%20take%20your%20400.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220766e18a-4931-414e-aa32-3292f1963bb1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPutting%20%2462%2C000%20worth%20of%20renovations%20into%20the%20property%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20McNeeley%20bought%20the%20duplex%2C%20one%20of%20the%20units%20was%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20destroyed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20needed%20drywall%2C%20plumbing%2C%20electric.%20It%20wasn't%20livable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20unit%20he%20moved%20into%20wasn't%20much%20better.%20It%20was%20%26quot%3Bclose%20to%20not%20livable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20described.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20he%20spent%20%2462%2C000%20and%2010%20months%20renovating.%20In%20May%202024%2C%20a%20tenant%20moved%20into%20the%20second%20unit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20appreciation%20of%20the%20last%20year%20and%20the%20other%20unit%20being%20rented%2C%20the%20property%20is%20worth%20about%20%24700%2C000%2C%20so%20I've%20made%20close%20to%20%24300%2C000%20in%20profit%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McNeeley%2C%20who%20bought%20the%20house%20in%20cash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAvoiding%20financing%20was%20important%20to%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20problems%20with%20the%20BRRRR%20method%20is%20the%20funding%20source%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20'repair'%20part%20of%20BRRRR%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20borrow%20hard%20money%20because%20they%20want%20to%20buy%20a%20property%20that%20you%20can't%20get%20traditional%20lending%20on.%20That%20hard%20money%20will%20have%20a%20higher%20interest%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20and%20usually%20within%20six%20months%20or%20a%20year%20the%20interest%20rate%20goes%20up%20a%20lot%2C%20so%20you%20want%20to%20get%20the%20repairs%20done%20and%20get%20it%20rented%20out%20within%20that%20six%20months%20or%20a%20year%2C%20whatever%20your%20timeline%20is%2C%20and%20then%20refinance%20to%20a%20traditional%20mortgage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20bought%20in%20cash%20to%20avoid%20the%20time%20crunch.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227cd4f45f-a96b-4d1d-bdb2-20be7d59e393%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20price%20of%20doing%20a%20'live-in%20BRRRR'%3A%20Living%20in%20a%20construction%20zone%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20'live-in%20BRRRR'%20has%20been%20lucrative%20for%20McNeeley.%20When%20he%20started%20the%20project%2C%20he%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20unit%20of%20one%20of%20his%20properties%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%94%3Cspan%3E%20a%20fourplex%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%94%20%3Cspan%3Eand%20filled%20it%20with%20a%20tenant.%20Now%20that%20all%20four%20units%20are%20rented%2C%20the%20property%20is%20%26quot%3Balmost%20making%20%244%2C000%20a%20month%20without%20me%20living%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20McNeeley%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20moved%20into%20the%20duplex%2C%20which%20he%20purchased%20in%20cash%2C%20so%20he%20doesn't%20have%20a%20mortgage.%20He%20pays%20taxes%20and%20insurance%2C%20but%20the%20unit%20he%20fixed%20up%20rents%20for%20%242%2C125%20a%20month%20and%20more%20than%20covers%20his%20expenses%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20I'm%20being%20paid%20to%20live%20where%20I'm%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20major%20tradeoff%20was%20living%20in%20a%20construction%20zone%20and%20without%20a%20kitchen%20and%20bathroom%20for%20months%20during%20the%20renovation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20literally%20go%20to%20the%20state%20park%20up%20the%20street%20to%20take%20showers.%20It%20was%20almost%20like%20camping%20for%20two%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McNeeley.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20willing%20to%20do%20some%20things%20that%20people%20aren't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8444187-21c7-47ea-a381-6de8d1db02aa%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat's%20next%3F%20A%20cash-out%20refi%20or%20selling%20and%20avoiding%20up%20to%20%24250%2C000%20in%20capital%20gains%20tax%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20that%20the%20rehab%20is%20complete%2C%20the%20next%20step%20of%20the%20BRRRR%20method%20would%20be%20to%20refinance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20do%20a%20cash-out%20refinance%20and%20get%20my%20money%20back%20because%20I've%20added%20the%20value%20to%20the%20property%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20take%20%24500%2C000%20or%20%24600%2C000%20out%20and%20go%20buy%20another%20rental%20and%20increase%20my%20cash%20flow.%20That's%20a%20good%20outcome.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOr%2C%20he%20could%20divert%20from%20the%20BRRRR%20and%20sell%20the%20property.%20This%20option%20intrigues%20him%20because%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-flipping-couple-explain-how-they-avoid-capital-gains-tax-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%20121%20Exclusion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20an%20IRS%20rule%20that%20lets%20taxpayers%20exclude%20up%20to%20%24250%2C000%20of%20the%20gain%20from%20the%20sale.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20main%20requirement%20is%20that%20you%20must%20use%20the%20home%20as%20your%20main%20residence%20for%20at%20least%20two%20of%20the%20five%20years%20preceding%20the%20sale%2C%20which%20McNeeley%20will%20satisfy%20in%20July%202025.%20If%20you're%20selling%20a%20vacation%20home%2C%20for%20example%2C%20you%20can't%20use%20the%20exclusion.%20You%20can%20also%20only%20use%20the%20exclusion%20every%20two%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20sell%20it%2C%20make%20a%20couple%20hundred%20thousand%20dollars%20in%20profit%2C%20and%20not%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20penny%20in%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20either%20go%20and%20repeat%20the%20process%20somewhere%20else%20or%20go%20buy%20something%20with%20the%20gains%20and%20have%20a%20bigger%2C%20nicer%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20likely%20won't%20do%20another%20live-in%20BRRRR%20because%20of%20the%20rougher%20living%20conditions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20probably%20won't%20know%20until%20July%20when%20I%20have%20an%20appraisal%20done%20on%20if%20I'm%20going%20to%20do%20a%20cash-out%20refinance%20or%20I'm%20going%20to%20sell%20the%